schemas.name: access_key
schemas.description:
The access key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

schemas.name: external_id
schemas.description: The external ID to use when assuming the role. If omitted, no external ID is passed to the AssumeRole call.

schemas.name: policy
schemas.description: The permissions applied when assuming a role. You cannot use, this policy to grant further permissions that are in excess to those of the,  role that is being assumed.

schemas.name: role_arn
schemas.description: The ARN of an IAM role to assume prior to making API calls.

schemas.name: session_name
schemas.description: The session name to use when assuming the role. If omitted, no session name is passed to the AssumeRole call.

schemas.name: max_retries
schemas.description:
The maximum number of times an AWS API request is
being executed. If the API request still fails, an error is
thrown.

schemas.name: profile
schemas.description:
The profile for API operations. If not set, the default profile
created with `aws configure` will be used.

schemas.name: region
schemas.description:
The region where AWS operations will take place. Examples
are us-east-1, us-west-2, etc.

schemas.name: s3_force_path_style
schemas.description:
Set this to true to force the request to use path-style addressing,
i.e., http://s3.amazonaws.com/BUCKET/KEY. By default, the S3 client will
use virtual hosted bucket addressing when possible
(http://BUCKET.s3.amazonaws.com/KEY). Specific to the Amazon S3 service.

schemas.name: secret_key
schemas.description:
The secret key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

schemas.name: shared_credentials_file
schemas.description:
The path to the shared credentials file. If not set
this defaults to ~/.aws/credentials.

schemas.name: skip_credentials_validation
schemas.description: Skip the credentials validation via STS API. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have STS available/implemented.

schemas.name: skip_get_ec2_platforms
schemas.description: Skip getting the supported EC2 platforms. Used by users that don't have ec2:DescribeAccountAttributes permissions.

schemas.name: skip_region_validation
schemas.description: Skip static validation of region name. Used by users of alternative AWS-like APIs or users w/ access to regions that are not public (yet).

schemas.name: skip_requesting_account_id
schemas.description: Skip requesting the account ID. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have IAM/STS API and/or metadata API.

schemas.name: token
schemas.description:
session token. A session token is only required if you are
using temporary security credentials.

schemas.name: stage_key
schemas.deprecated: Since the API Gateway usage plans feature was launched on August 11, 2016, usage plans are now required to associate an API key with an API stage

schemas.name: min_adjustment_step
schemas.deprecated: Use min_adjustment_magnitude instead, otherwise you may see a perpetual diff on this resource.

schemas.name: timeout

schemas.name: number_of_connections
